cs.CV, cs.AR, cs.NE, cs.SY, cs.LG 

This paper focuses on the acceleration of 2D and 3D DCNNs, which are commonly used in computer vision applications (cs.CV). The proposed efficient schemes for mapping DCNNs on a uniform architecture involve hardware optimization techniques (cs.AR) and aim to improve both throughput and energy efficiency (cs.NE). The implementation is done on an FPGA platform (cs.SY), and the paper also discusses comparisons with CPU and GPU solutions, which are topics related to machine learning and optimization (cs.LG).
